            <h2>Section 1: The True Cost of Mattress Removal in 2026</h2>

            <p>According to the Mattress Recycling Council, Americans discard more than <strong>50,000 mattresses daily</strong>—roughly 18 million annually. The Product Stewardship Institute estimates that less than 10% are recycled nationally, with the rate dropping below 5% in states without mandatory recycling programs. Understanding disposal costs has never been more important as landfill tipping fees rise and more states consider recycling mandates.</p>

            <h3 id="section-1-1">1.1 National Cost Overview</h3>

            <p>According to HomeGuide and Angi pricing surveys, the national average for professional mattress removal falls between <strong>$100-$250</strong>. However, costs vary dramatically based on disposal method, mattress size, and geographic location.</p>

            <p>A Bedder World's analysis of over 1.15 million mattress removals across all 50 states shows an average cost of <strong>$135</strong>. This reflects the company's focus on recycling-first disposal, which requires transportation to certified recycling facilities rather than the nearest landfill.</p>

